com.github.unix_junkie.javafs

Class FileSystemEntry

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.unix_junkie.javafs.FileSystemEntry
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    Directory, File, SymbolicLink

    public abstract class FileSystemEntry
extends Object

    File system entry, a common superclass of File, Directory and SymbolicLink.

    Author:
    Andrew ``Bass'' Shcheglov <mailto:andrewbass@gmail.com>
    See Also:
    File, Directory, SymbolicLink

    • Field Detail

      • dataSize

        protected long dataSize
        If a child entry is added to or removed from a directory, its size gets updated.

      • name

        @Nonnull
protected final String name
        The name of this file system entry w/o the directory part (the basename).

      • source

        @Nullable
protected Path source
        For a detached entry, may contain the source of this entry at the external file system. For attached entries (i.e. those which have been already written to the local file system) is always null.

protected FileSystem fileSystem

      • FileSystemEntry

        protected FileSystemEntry(Path source)
                   throws IOException

      • FileSystemEntry

        protected FileSystemEntry(PosixAttributes attributes,
                          byte numberOfLinks,
                          short uid,
                          short gid,
                          long dataSize,
                          Date creationTime,
                          Date modificationTime,
                          Date accessTime,
                          String name,
                          @Nullable
                          ByteBuffer encodedName)

        Creates a detached file system entry from the complete metadata.

        Parameters:
        attributes - POSIX attributes.
        numberOfLinks - number of hard links.
        uid - owner Id (UID).
        gid - group Id (GID).
        dataSize - the data length of this entry.
        creationTime - creation time.
        modificationTime - modification time.
        accessTime - access time.
        name - the name of this file or directory (just the last name in the pathname's name sequence).
        encodedName - name encoded into a byte array, or null.
